You are correct that I mean `str(func_or_lambda)`.  I think this would be well complimented by changing the `equals` function as follows.

```python
def equals(value):
    def inner(other):
        return other == value
    inner.__name__ = "is_equal_to_{0}".format(value)
    return inner
```

This way our auto-generated functions will have helpful string representations.

One thing that isn't ideal about this is that `equals('arst') != equals('arst')` since the generated functions won't be equivalent.  I think we can fix this with some class shenanigans.

```python
class Equals:
    def __init__(self, value):
        self.value = value
    def __call__(self, other):
        return self.value == other
    def __eq__(self, other):
        return isinstance(other, Equals) and self.value == other.value
```

There are probably a few more dunder methods that need to be implemented like `__hash__`.

